<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101853545621934></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101853545621934><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=101853545621934>RE: How do i solo</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=101853545621934#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=81363><span id=Scholar>Jabbezz</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>17 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Apr 11th 10:36 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Certainly they can solo and quite well if you know what you are doing.&nbsp;&nbsp;I spent levels 25 to 32 leveling in Everfrost.  Camp out near the ever popular Mammoth Platform to the west of the Permafrost zone.  This spot is safe to med and buff up.  Keep SoW and regen up... use Cannibalize occasionally and then run around the area looking for the big mommas.  Hit em with Malise, run a little way, cast root, dot, frost strike 3 times... med until root breaks, melee 5 or 6 hits and collect the tusks which sell for 8 to 10pp each.  Feel free to email me if you have specific questions.<br>Elihu - 34th Shaman<br>Jabbezz - 36th Paladin<br>&nbsp;<br>Give me a place whereon to stand,a fulcrum strong enough,a lever long enough, and I will move the world</td></tr>
