<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101800300672216></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101800300672216><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=101800300672216>another 2cp</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=101800300672216#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=147821><span id=Sage>Aggrok</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>69 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Apr 5th 5:41 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Last night I finally hit level 50. I have spent levels 42-50 in The Dreadlands, mostly in small parties of 2-3 people--shaman have the luxury of being able to pick a melee class and maybe another healer/melee/nuker class to gain XP very fast--at this level you do not need a full party to fight low blues/light blue mobs--A 50 shaman paired with say a reasonable well equipped monk or warrior can almost chain pull with little down time if you space the buffing so that all your tanks/pets buffs do not die at once. I have no real special gear like a fungi tunic or mana regen items either, so this is doable by any shaman who, as I said in my last post, have invested time and effort into melee ability. I finally broke down and spent 500pp training my 2hb in the Oggok guild to reach 193 as I hadnt had a skill up in seemingly forever ( of course after that i got 2 skill ups in 2hb and am now at 195 2hb ). With our level 49 spells we can easily reach 255 STR and over 200 DEX. I have now been able to hit for a maximum of 155 hp in a single blow in melee combat. I have noticed that some of the best 3rd members to have are mages and wizards, since at that level they pretty much know how to play the class and not get aggro--they require very little effort from the shaman buff-wise and can speed up encounters a great deal. Rogues are great too as usually all they need is haste and maybe a few stat buffs ( I have JB arms, gloves, and helm for mana free STR, DEX, and CHA buffs ). Our level 49 pet is SOOOO much better than the 44 one--at 48 the best pet was light blue the rest green--I've only summoned dark blue pets at 49 now--they can solo alot of the easier mobs in DL with just haste and a slowed mob. I would suggest if you are just going to pair up that you pick a warrior or monk atleast level 47+ so you dont have to burn mana healing them constantly ( still 1 level away from superior heal...grrr. ). There is almost no way a shaman can tank with a 1hb/piercing weapon unless the have an iceworm fang or the epic--the just dont do enough damage. A full group will have to pull nearly 3 times as fast as a shaman / tank combo to make the same XP--the problem with this is that say your puller in a full group is pulling pairs--well you absolutlety must get them slowed asap--well then you sit down to med and atleast one of them will come and try to cream you ( I accidently slowed myself the other night with Togors--no wonder the mobs hate it so much--i was very irritated at my own stupidity hehe ). Then you have to stand there and take hits till a tank can taunt the mob off of you--might as well melee it if you can while its trying to return you to your bind point in that bad kinda way. My next trip to Oggok I will go ahead and max my 2hb skill out ( at 50pp+ per point now...ouch) and I should be slightly over 1000 attack rating. One thing alot of shaman dont really think about is that by the time the get their epic they will not be meleeing but rooting/rightclicking JBB ( I wish I had one ) and the epic they wont be hitting with their epic much at all, just casting its DoT effect, so theres really not a good reason to handicap yourself in lower levels with inferior piercing weapons--the right click on the epic will work the same if your piercing skill is 2 or 200. I have outpaced many of my shaman friends who were the same level as I was at one time ( low 20's ) not due to more play time but due to better tactics. Also, atleast from my obsevation, 90% of the groups formed in DL are &quot;pick-up&quot; groups where the party members may not know each other well, if at all..I've seen way more deaths in full groups from miscommuncation, not following the leaders advice etc--with 2 people its very easy to know what you and his/her role is at all times--come to think of it Ive never had a partner die and we maybe had to zone twice in 8 levels of XP there--things just run more smoothly with the fewest amount of people required for a given task. Shaman is a rather uniques class, and no we cant quad kite but there are very few 2 person combos that can pull at any reasonable rate on XP giving mobs ( paladin/ enchanter comes to mind also) . Use the class for all its potential and you will not be disappointed--and--most importantly--HAVE FUN--heck the last group I was in we let the enchanter melee some just for kicks--I think he landed one blow for 2 damage ( was funny watching a werewolf miss like he'd been drinking !) And please, I am not professing to know it all, and will admit I have never been to the planes yet or in a massive multi party raid--I'm just saying what has worked well for me--I find it much more satisfying to have made 50 having to think my thru situations rather that have 3 level 60's PL me to 50 in 2 days play time ( not knocking that either..to each his own.) Well thatll be all for now--if you have any questions for me Ill try to give ya an honest answer--look up Aggrok on Luclin server--later all.......<br>50 Ogre Battleshaman on Luclin--Aggrok<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
