	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Mar 19th 10:13 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi there Bejn<br>Here are a few tips from a friend shaman of mine<br>lets see at lvl 43 head on up to Rathe Mtns and solo HGs.<br><br>1. summon pet<br>2. buff up pet with hp buff, str, dex and always keep up haste on him.<br>3. buff yourself up with hp buff, sta, str, dex, agi, chloro and of course sow and haste.<br>4. now have pet sit down somewhere, pull yourself a HG with slow.<br>5. run him to where your doggie is and sick him on HG.<br>6. now you dot the freakin thing with VoS (venom of snake) and Scrouge. (I know people hate scrouge cause it takes a long time but it works).<br>7. join pet in the fight.<br>8. if VoS wears off enstill HG back up dot it again and maybe heal yourself. (pet can take a beating for a bit)<br>9. go in again, if VoS wears off again dot it again.<br>10. by this time it should start running and you get decent exp plus money onto that.<br>11. you will definitely raise your Defense by a lot.<br><br>So that's just a tip from a shaman friend of mine, he's a lvl 49 shaman on Luclin.&nbsp;&nbsp;GL to ya :)<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
