	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yes shamans cant really compete with chanters and bards at times, but from what ive seen you need to get a few more levels. Now that Luclin is out shaman are more desireable than ever, especially once we get the group buffs at 56+, and with AA skills we can even AE buff. Im not there yet but im close. By the way I personally cannot recall a single instance where I was not welcomed into a group or had a chanter or bard taken before me. More times than not when i see people LFG, I see something like this: &quot; Group seeking a sower&quot;, &quot;Party of 5 needs a healer, PST&quot;, or &quot; Group seeks a shaman or enchanter&quot;. Yes alot of our&nbsp;&nbsp;spells are similar to an enchanter, but we can heal and SoW too. LOL, I have never seen a group specifically ask for a ranger or any INT caster for that matter, not that they arent needed but are usually in a group with 4 other melee classes and no healer/sower/haster/slower--so they ask for us. Only clerics and enchanters are asked for as much or more. In a huge raid they are going to need a shaman and no one is going to turn you down unless they dont have enough keys to go around. Enchanters love us because they already get a huge amount of aggro from tash, mezzing, charms and debuffs--they'd much rather have someone else cast slow and malo-whatever you have. Druids do have more group buffs than us early on, but we catch up in the end. Every class has its value, so dont not ( double negative intended )pick a shaman just because of what others say--if you play well you will always be welcome wherever you go, no matter what class you play.<br><br>54 Ogre Battleshaman on Luclin server--Aggrok<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
