	   <tr><td colspan=2>Best Race:&nbsp;&nbsp;Nobody's mentioned Vah Shir yet.... They are not KOS anywhere until you start changing your faction.  I don't know much about Barbarians, but the Vah Shir begin with decent stats all around.  Also consider the Vah Shir race because of their - <br><br>Starting City:  Shar Vahl and Shadeweaver's Thicket are great starting cities.  You level fast and make good money.  Several ridiculously easy quests will outfit your character from head to toe, and many of the quests give you nice magic goodies.  You could easily stay in those two zones from 1-15.<br><br>Strategy:  I don't have much to offer besides that I didn't group at all from 1-10.  No need to.  Soloed blue and black mobs, healed myself with Inner Fire.  Buy Spirit Pouch early, 'cause you're gonna need all the loot carrying capacity you can get!  Unfortunately, the DOTs might not be sold in Shar Vahl.  I couldn't find any low level DOT spells, and eventually ran to Everfrost to pick some up.<br><br>Weapon:  Keep your options open.  I'm disappointed with their choice of weapons, especially in the early levels.  You never know when a good weapon will present itself, when some generous soul will give you something sweet.<br><br>Misc. Tips:  Follow the advice of others, I sure didn't - I wasted at least five points in other starting stats when I should have dumped them into WIS.  Your buffs even at early levels make up for the other stats, and WIS items seem hard to come by.  <br>&nbsp;<br>Phreda Biggles<br>34 Warrior, Drunken Bandit<br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=122873 target=_new>Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl</a></td></tr>
